cs213.photoAlbum.model

Interface User

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    MyUser

    public interface User
    User Interface describes the user object. A user has a unique ID,albums, and a name. The id and name can be set and they can be returned by the get methods. Albums can be added to the user and removed. Also, albums can be renamed if the new name does not conflict with existing album.
    Author:
    Nadiia Chepurko

        java.util.List<Album> getAlbums()

      • addAlbum

        void addAlbum(Album albumImpl)
        Adds a new album to the user. Only an album with a unique name can be added. A single user may not have duplicate album names, but the album name may be duplicated across users.
        Parameters:
        albumImpl - The album to be added.

      • deleteAlbum

        void deleteAlbum(java.lang.String albumName)
        Deletes an existing album from the user. If the user does not have the specified album nothing is done.
        Parameters:
        albumName - Name of the album to be deleted.

      • renameAlbum

        void renameAlbum(java.lang.String oldAlbumName,
                 java.lang.String newAlbumName)
        Renames an existing album of a user. An album can be renamed if the new name does not conflict with an existing album name.
        Parameters:
        oldAlbumName - The name of the old album to be renamed.
        newAlbumName - The new name of that album.
